(24, 0, 'Nisarga Tulsi/Tulasi Pot Plastic Terracotta Painted Colour', 'simple', 'P102', '<ul>\r\\n  <li>Durable Planter light in weight, with provision for drain holes</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> For all type of indoor plants, tabletop plants, herbs, and even vegetables, outdoor plant</li>\r\\n  <li>19.1 (H) X 14 CM</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n ', 'Tulasi / Tulsi Pot Terracotta Color Planter Lord Ganesh, Shiva, Lakshmi, Krishna on 4 sides of the planter Made from 100% Virgin Plastic - Lasts many years even in sun UV Stabilized Plastic Planter Thick-walled, Don\'t break easily Tulasi/Tulsi Planter X 1 QTY Easy Gardening is the leading provider of Plastic pots and accessories used in home gardens in India. Minerva Naturals markets various kinds of Plastic Pots, Orchid Pots, Hanging Pots, Net Pots, Root Trainers and Accessories. Easy\r\\n\r\\nGardening Plastic pots and accessories are designed and manufactured maintaining the highest quality standards. Easy Gardening Pots are designed to be durable, light in weight, easily stock-able, with large drain holes and, are cost-effective for the grower.\r\\n\r\\nTulsi pot terracotta color, it can be used in outdoor or indoor. High-quality plastic and none fade able to color. Best for medium size plants.', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '[]', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 0, '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '199', 'Plastic Pot, Tulsi pot', '', '', '', '', '', 'nisarga-tulsitulasi-pot-plastic-terracotta-painted-colour', ''),
(25, 0, 'ZZ Plant, Zamioculcas Zamiifolia Plant, Aroid palm', 'variable', 'A122', '<ul>\r\\n  <li>The plant comes in two size options.</li>\r\\n  <li>10-12\" tall plant in a 4\" pot</li>\r\\n  <li>14-20\" tall plant in a 6\" pot</li>\r\\n  <li>Perennial plant and remains green throughout the year.</li>\r\\n  <li>Excellent <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zamioculcas#Air_purification\">air purifier</a> and removes toxins from the air.</li>\r\\n  <li>Useful in home decor, garden decor, and gift purposes.</li>\r\\n  <li>Plants can survive in low light.</li>\r\\n</ul>', '<h2>ZZ Plant, Aroid Palm</h2>\r\\n<strong>ZZ plant (Zamioculcas zamiifolia)</strong> is a tropical plant in the Araceae family of <a href=\"https://www.espoma.com/gardening/indoor-gardening/whats-an-aroid/\">aroids</a>. It is also known as the Aroid palm and Zanzibar Gem. It comes from Zanzibar, Kenya, and other parts of Eastern Africa. it is a slow-growing, <strong>easy-to-care</strong>-for houseplant. ZZ has characteristic oval-shaped, thick waxy dark green leaves. It is a low-maintenance, drought-resistant plant that is perfect for beginning gardeners because it demands very little watering and attention.\r\\n\r\\n \r\\n<h3 id=\"zz-plant-rhizomes\"><strong>Rhizomes</strong></h3>\r\\nUnder the surface of the soil, you might see big rhizomes that look like potatoes. Since these plants grew up in drier conditions than most other aroids, they have rhizomes that store water to help them survive drought in their natural habitat. With the help of these underground rhizomes, the plant slowly moves to new places and grows new leaves as it goes.\r\\n<h3 id=\"zz-plant-rhizomes\"><strong>Soil & fertilizer</strong></h3>\r\\nAs long as there is adequate drainage in the potting medium, ZZ plants are not overly picky about what they are given. The majority of standard potting mixes should be adequate for the plant. no need for adding extra fertilizers. If there is a need for more drainage, adding some perlite, gravel, or sand to the mix will help.\r\\n<div class=\"section-title-container cell medium-4 large-3\">\r\\n<h2 class=\"section-title\">ZZ Care</h2>\r\\n</div>\r\\n<div class=\"content-container cell medium-8 large-9\">\r\\n<div class=\"plant-care-container\">\r\\n<h4 class=\"section-content\">?? Sunlight:</h4>\r\\nCan withstand practically any intensity of light without getting damaged. while it is recommended to keep the plant in bright indirect sunlight. whereas direct sunlight may scorch its leaves.\r\\n<h4 class=\"section-content\">??Watering:</h4>\r\\nZZ is a drought-tolerant?plant and hence demands very little watering. Watering sessions should be once-twice a week depending on soil dryness and humidity in the air.\r\\n\r\\n \r\\n\r\\n</div>\r\\n<h6 class=\"section-content\">Also Check:</h6>\r\\n<div class=\"plant-care-container\">\r\\n<p class=\"section-content\">?The <a href=\"https://nurserynisarga.in/product/zamioculcas-zamiifolia-black/\">ZZ Raven Plant</a> is a fashionable and easy-to-care-for houseplant with new growth that emerges in brilliant dark green coloration and swiftly develops into rich, black, dark leaves. ?</p>\r\\n\r\\n</div>\r\\n</div>', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '[]', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 0, '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '199', 'aroid palm, indoor, less requirements, low light, low maintenance palm, Zamia palm, Zamioculcas Zamiifolia, zz, ZZ plant', '', '', '', '', '', 'zz-plant-zamioculcas-zamiifolia-plant-aroid-palm', ''),
(26, 0, 'White Orchid Plant - Dendrobium Orchid With Pot', 'simple', 'A123', '&nbsp;\r\\n<ul>\r\\n  <li>Live plant along with Plastic pot.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\"></i> Plants height with pot is 1 feet and pot size is 5-inch diameter.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\"></i> Plants nature is indoor-semi shade, watering once in 5 days.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\"></i> Useful for gifts Plants, table top Plants, indoor flowering.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\"></i> Beautiful texture, hardy plant & low maintenance.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n ', '<div id=\"tab-description\" class=\"tab-pane tab-content active\">\r\\n<div id=\"tab-description\" class=\"tab-pane tab-content active\">\r\\n<h3>Dendrobium Orchid</h3>\r\\nThere are over 1,000 types of Dendrobium orchids and hybrids. They vary in size, bloom color, appearance, and growing requirements. For this reason, it is important that you get detailed care information for your certain type of Dendrobium because the care can greatly vary depending on the type you have.\r\\n\r\\n<strong>Dendrobium Water Requirements</strong>\r\\nA Dendrobium Nobile orchid should be watered in the morning using lukewarm water. Watering frequency ? as covered in this article about watering orchids ? can be determined by a few different things. The watering schedule for a Den-Nobile greatly depends on the season and its growth cycle. When the plant is actively growing, you should water once a week. In the early fall, you should reduce your watering schedule to help encourage bud growth. In the winter you should only water when you see that the pseudobulbs are beginning to shrivel because this is an indicator that you are not giving the plant enough water.\r\\n\r\\n<strong>Dendrobium Light Requirements</strong>\r\\nDen-Nobile orchids, along with it?s hybrids, grow best with high light intensity. The ideal place for a Den-Nobile is a windowsill with southern light exposure. Remember to not let the orchid receive direct sunlight because this could cause the orchid to get sunburned leaves.\r\\n\r\\n<strong>Dendrobium Temperature Requirements</strong>\r\\nDendrobium Nobile orchids are cooler growers than the Den-Phals and they require temperatures that are a little lower. While the Den-Nobile orchid is in bloom it does best with nighttime temperatures of 40?F to 50?F (4.4?C to 10?C). Temperatures should not rise above 90?F (32.2?C) or fall below 37?F to 39?F (2.8?C to 3.9?C).\r\\n\r\\n<strong>Dendrobium Humidity Requirements</strong>\r\\nAs covered in this ?humidity? article on how to care for orchids, Den-Nobile orchids do best with a humidity level of 50-60%. You will want to make sure to maintain good air movement to help prevent orchid disease from setting in.\r\\n\r\\n<strong>Dendrobium Fertilizer Requirements</strong>\r\\nWhen Den-Nobile orchids are in full growth they should be fertilized regularly. It is important to never fertilize an orchid that is completely dry, because doing so can cause major damage to the roots.\r\\n\r\\n<strong>Dendrobium Potting Requirements</strong>\r\\nDen-Nobile orchids should be repotted every year and a half to two years or once the canes have begun to overgrow the pot or the potting medium remains soggy and no longer drains properly. Only repot the orchid after it has bloomed. Before repotting always trim away the damaged roots with a sterile cutting tool. Den-Nobile orchids can be divided as long as they have 7 or 8 canes. If you were to divide a plant with less than that it would stunt the growth of each division.\r\\n\r\\n</div>\r\\n</div>', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '[]', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 0, '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '699', '750', 'Dendrobium Orchid Purple, Orchid Plant with Flower, white orchid', '', '', '', '', '', 'white-orchid-plant-dendrobium-orchid-with-pot', ''),
