(327, 0, 'Rabbit foot Fern, Davallia fejeensis', 'variable', 'MF-8748', '<ul>\r\\n  <li>Live Bushy plant along with the coloured plastic pot.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>The plant covers the 4 & 6-inch diameter of the pot.</li>\r\\n  <li>Also available in 8inch dia pot, in excel size, more bushy</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>plants\' nature is indoor/semi-shaded, less watering.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>Recommended by air purifying study.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>Best hanging plants, useful for tabletop and gift plants.</li>\r\\n</ul>', '<i><b>Davallia fejeensis</b></i>?is a species of?<a title=\"Fern\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fern\">fern</a>?in the family?<a class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Davalliaceae\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Davalliaceae\">Davalliaceae</a>, commonly referred to as Rabbit?s Foot Fern. They are best known for their furry, brown, and yellow rhizomes, which looks like a rabbit?s foot, hence the name.\r\\n\r\\nIt is native to the?<a class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fiji Islands\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fiji_Islands\">Fiji Islands</a>?in?<a title=\"Oceania\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oceania\">Oceania</a>. They survive from approximately 60-75?F (15-24?C) and cannot survive below 55?F (13?C). They can grow up to 2 ft at the most.', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '[]', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 0, '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '199', 'Davallia fejeensis, fern, fern plant, Green plant, Indoor Plant, maidenhair fern, nursery nisarga, plant online, rabbit foot fern, small plants, tabletop plant', '', '', '', '', '', 'rabbit-foot-fern-davallia-fejeensis', ''),
(328, 0, 'Brahmi plant- Indian pennywort, herb of grace', 'simple', 'BP-7868', '<ul class=\"list-unstyled\">\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?Live plant along with coloured plastic pot and tray</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?plants height with pot is 1 feet and pot size is 4 icnhes height.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?plants nature is outdoor, alternate day watering</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?useful for medicinal Plant, shrubs</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?hardy and easy maintenance</li>\r\\n</ul>', '<h3><span class=\"w8qArf\">Brahmi plant- Indian Pennywort, Herb of Grace</span></h3>\r\\n<strong><span class=\"w8qArf\">Scientific name<span class=\"eTVOZd\">:</span>?</span><span class=\"LrzXr kno-fv wHYlTd z8gr9e\">Bacopa monnieri</span></strong>\r\\n\r\\nBacopa monnieri is a very popular herb in India for longevity and mental function. It is used to decrease fatigue and depression, and to stimulate the sex drive. It energizes the central nervous system, and aids the circulatory system, soothes and minimizes varicose veins and helps to minimize scarring. It is also useful in repairing skin and connective tissues and smoothing out cellulite. It is generally considered an Ayurvedic \"age tonic\" restoring youth and vitality.\r\\n\r\\n<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bacopa_monnieri\">Brahmi</a> (Bacopa monnieri) has been used by Ayurveda in India for almost 3000 years. The Ayurvedic treatise, the Charaka Samhita (100 A.D.), recommends Brahmi in formulations for a range of mental conditions including anxiety, poor cognition and lack of concentration. In India, Brahmi is currently recognized as being effective in the treatment of mental illness and epilepsy.', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '[]', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 0, '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '325', 'herb of grace., Indian pennywort, thyme-leafed gratiola, water hyssop', '', '', '', '', '', 'brahmi-plant-indian-pennywort-herb-of-grace', ''),
(329, 0, 'Ipomoea, Morning Glory Plant', 'simple', 'IP-7657', '<ul class=\"list-unstyled\">\r\\n  <li>?Live plant along with the coloured plastic pot and tray.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?plants height with pot is 1 feet and pot size is 6 inches in height.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?plants nature is outdoor-semi shade, alternate day watering.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?useful for garden, landscaping & entrance, grows up to 10 feet.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?Best flowering climber & beautiful flowers, hardy and easy maintenance.</li>\r\\n</ul>', '<h3 class=\"product-title\">Ipomoea, Morning Glory Plant</h3>\r\\nIpomoea is the largest genus in the flowering plant family Convolvulaceae, with over 600 species. It is a large and diverse group with common names including morning glory, water convolvulus or Kang Kung, sweet potato, bindweed, moonflower, etc.', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '[]', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 0, '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '599', 'ipomea, ipomea plant, pink, purple, small flowes, violet', '', '', '', '', '', 'ipomoea-morning-glory-plant', ''),
(330, 0, 'Decora Premium square pot \"Code - GC\"', 'variable', 'DECO101-3', 'Finish: Matt\r\\nColour: Grey/White Stone\r\\nUpper Dia: 30 cm\r\\nLower Dia: 30 cm\r\\nDepth: 26 cm', '<div id=\"productTabContent\" class=\"tab-content\">\r\\n<div id=\"product_tabs_description\" class=\"tab-pane fade in active\">\r\\n<div class=\"std\">\r\\n<div id=\"productTabContent\" class=\"tab-content\">\r\\n<div id=\"product_tabs_description\" class=\"tab-pane fade in active\">\r\\n<div class=\"std\">\r\\n<div class=\"woocommerce-product-details__short-description\">\r\\n\r\\nDecora GC? Grey/White Stone Planter\r\\n\r\\nUser-friendly and simple, these Plastic fibre pots are equipped with spaces for fitting screws for easy attachment. With a distinctive round shape with extended rims, these pots offer a large number of options to the gardener on deciding which plants to grow.\r\\nplanters with textured finish are tough, lightweight alternatives to clay or ceramic planters. Each planter?s rolled lip offers added durability.\r\\n\r\\nFinish: Matt\r\\nColour: Grey/White Stone\r\\nUpper Dia: 30 cm\r\\nLower Dia: 30 cm\r\\nDepth: 26 cm\r\\n\r\\n</div>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n  <li>Fibre material.</li>\r\\n  <li>Non-fading</li>\r\\n  <li>Lightweight</li>\r\\n  <li>Zero maintenance</li>\r\\n  <li>Durable</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n</div>\r\\n</div>\r\\n</div>\r\\n</div>\r\\n</div>\r\\n</div>', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '[]', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 0, '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '199', 'decora, decora pots, Decora premium pots', '', '', '', '', '', 'decora-premium-square-pot-code-gc', ''),
(331, 0, 'Red Anthurium Plant, Laceleaf', 'variable', 'KA-5647', '<ul>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>Live plant along with the colored plastic pot.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>Plants height with pot is 1 feet and pot size is 6-inch diameter.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>Best house plants, flowering plants, easy maintenance.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>Easy to grow in any climate, annual plants, fast-growing.</li>\r\\n</ul>', '<h5>Anthurium, Flamingo Flower, Laceleaf, Tailflower Plant</h5>\r\\nAnthuriums plant is the world?s longest blooming houseplant ? they are rarely without their showy blooms! Each bloom can last up to eight weeks, and new ones will pop up often. These aren?t actual flowers, but modified waxy leaves. Anthuriums flourish and bloom best in bright indirect light.\r\\n\r\\nArrives in a nursery grow nestled inside our decorative planter.\r\\n\r\\n<strong>Plant Care:-</strong>\r\\n\r\\nType: Annual Flowering\r\\n\r\\nBlooming: Spring, Summer, Fall, Winter\r\\n\r\\nCategory: Flowering Shrub\r\\n<div class=\"plant-care-container\">\r\\n\r\\n<img class=\"section-image light ls-is-cached lazyloaded\" src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0150/6262/t/137/assets/pdp_icon_light.svg?v=4400775217377875679\" alt=\"Sun icon\" width=\"101\" height=\"101\">\r\\n<p class=\"section-content\">Bright indirect to medium light</p>\r\\n\r\\n</div>\r\\n<div class=\"plant-care-container\">\r\\n\r\\n<img class=\"section-image water ls-is-cached lazyloaded\" src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0150/6262/t/137/assets/pdp_icon_water.svg?v=18168889493737383852\" alt=\"Water drops icon\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\">\r\\n<p class=\"section-content\">Water every 1?2 weeks</p>\r\\n\r\\n<h5>Common Problems</h5>\r\\nSYMPTOM:?Yellowing leaves\r\\nCAUSE:?Too much direct sunlight or overwatering\r\\n\r\\nSYMPTOM: New flowers are green instead of red or pink\r\\nCAUSE:?Too much sunlight\r\\n\r\\nSYMPTOM:?Flowers are turning pale green\r\\nCAUSE:?Underwatering, or temperature stress\r\\n\r\\nSYMPTOM:?Leaf elongation\r\\nCAUSE: Not enough light, or too far away from the light source\r\\n\r\\n</div>', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '[]', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 0, '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '199', 'anthurium, flamingo flower, king, king anthurium, laceleaf, Pigtail plant, tailflower', '', '', '', '', '', 'red-anthurium-plant-laceleaf', '');
