(931, 0, 'Buy Cinnamon Plant \"Dalchini\"', 'simple', 'Dalchini-897', '<h6><em>Botinical Name: Cinnamomum Verum</em></h6>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n  <li>Live plant along with Plastic pot.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Plants height with pot is 18-24 inches, 6 inches pot in diameter.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Plants nature is outdoor-semi shade.</li>\r\\n  <li>Water whenever the top two inches of soil have dried out.</li>\r\\n  <li>Cinnamon plants prefer a rich, well-draining soil.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Useful for edible Plants, herbs & medicinal plants.<i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i></li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n ', '<h2>Buy Cinnamon Plant \"Dalchini\"</h2>\r\\n<span class=\"Y2IQFc\" lang=\"en\"><b>Cinnamon</b> (Dalchini) is a spice obtained from the inner bark of several tree species from the? genus <a title=\"Cinnamomum\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cinnamomum\">Cinnamomum</a>. The bark of this tree is used as <a href=\"https://nurserynisarga.in/?s=medicine&post_type=product&dgwt_wcas=1\">medicine</a> and spices.</span><span class=\"Y2IQFc\" lang=\"en\">Cinnamon is a small evergreen tree, growing to 10?15 m (32.8?49.2 ft) tall. Cinnamon trees are mostly found in Sri Lanka and South India. The cinnamon plant produces tiny blooms, and its leaves are often bright green to yellow-green in colour. The bark and leaves have similar fragrances present. A \'variety of species\' inner bark is utilized to prepare seasoning. Cinnamon species can be planted in the spring or early fall and typically grow slowly to moderately. The smell of Cinnamon is pleasant, stimulates the senses, yet calms the nerves.</span>\r\\n<h5><span class=\"Y2IQFc\" lang=\"en\">Importance of </span>Cinnamon \"Dalchini\" in <span class=\"Y2IQFc\" lang=\"en\">Indian Food</span></h5>\r\\n<span class=\"Y2IQFc\" lang=\"en\">Indian Food is an aromatic mix of vibrantly coloured spices. These spices not only provide different tastes, but they also add an unique flavor to each dish to which they are added. Cinnamon powder is one of the most important spices used in the preparation of many Indian dishes.</span>\r\\n<h5>Interesting Fact<em>:</em></h5>\r\\nCinnamon is an excellent source of calcium and fiber. Cinnamon not only enhances the taste of food, but it is also an <a href=\"https://www.1mg.com/hi/patanjali/dalchini-ke-fayde/\">effective medicine</a>, controls blood sugar in the body.\r\\n<table class=\"mntl-sc-block-table__table\">\r\\n<tbody data-check=\"-1\">\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td><b>Plant Type</b></td>\r\\n<td>Tree, shrub</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td><b>Mature Size</b></td>\r\\n<td>3 to 16 feet tall, 2 to 6 ft. wide (depends on variety)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td><b>Sun Exposure</b></td>\r\\n<td>Full, partial</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td><b>Soil Type</b></td>\r\\n<td>Loamy, well-drained</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td><b>Soil pH</b></td>\r\\n<td>Acidic to neutral (6.2?7.2)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td><b>Bloom Time</b></td>\r\\n<td>Summer</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td><b>Flower Color</b></td>\r\\n<td>White, yellow</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td><b>Hardiness Zones</b></td>\r\\n<td>10?12 (USDA)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</table>', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '[]', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 0, '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '549', '699', 'Allspice, Elaichi, Indian bay Leaf, Medicinal plant', '', '', '', '', '', 'buy-cinnamon-plant-dalchini', ''),
(932, 0, 'Hanging Casuarina Plant', 'simple', 'HAN1286-1', 'The?<i>Casuarina</i> leaves are usually used for ornamental purposes in the urban region, very attractive and evergreen foliage, that looks like the feathers on the bird. Beautifully grow downward and have excellent commercial values\r\\n<ul class=\"list-unstyled\">\r\\n  <li>Live plant along with the plastic pot.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>Plants height with pot is 12-18 inches, downward and pot size is 6 inches diameter.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>Plants nature is outdoor, loves full sun.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>Best Evergreen foliage plants & beautiful color texture on leaves.</li>\r\\n  <li>Best for hanging and grow very fast.</li>\r\\n</ul>', '<h2>Hanging Casuarina Plant</h2>\r\\n<h6 xss=removed><strong>Hanging C<span class=\"tBJ dyH iFc sAJ O2T zDA IZT swG\"><span class=\"richPinInformation\"><span class=\"tBJ dyH iFc j1A O2T zDA IZT swG\">asuarina Available at Nursery Nisarga!</span></span></span></strong></h6>\r\\nThe Hanging C<span class=\"tBJ dyH iFc sAJ O2T zDA IZT swG\"><span class=\"richPinInformation\"><span class=\"tBJ dyH iFc j1A O2T zDA IZT swG\">asuarina </span></span></span>plant is a very attractive and evergreen tree textured evergreen foliage, that looks like the feathers on the bird., beautifully grow downward and have excellent commercial values, because it is highly versatile and can adapt to any environment. It improves soil conditions and can prevent soil erosion. <span class=\"tBJ dyH iFc sAJ O2T zDA IZT swG\"><span class=\"richPinInformation\"><span class=\"tBJ dyH iFc j1A O2T zDA IZT swG\">They are unusual for their elongated thorn like foliage and also used as an ornamental purpose.</span></span></span>\r\\n<h3>More about <span class=\"tBJ dyH iFc sAJ O2T zDA IZT swG\"><span class=\"richPinInformation\"><span class=\"tBJ dyH iFc j1A O2T zDA IZT swG\">Casuarina:</span></span></span></h3>\r\\n<div class=\"jzS ujU un8 TB_\">\r\\n<div class=\"Rnj hs0 un8 C9i\"><span class=\"tBJ dyH iFc sAJ O2T zDA IZT swG\"><span class=\"tBJ dyH iFc sAJ O2T zDA IZT swG\"><span class=\"richPinInformation\"><span class=\"tBJ dyH iFc j1A O2T zDA IZT swG\"><i><b>Casuarina</b></i>?is a?genus?of 17 tree species in the family?<a title=\"Casuarinaceae\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Casuarinaceae\">Casuarinaceae</a>, native to?Australia, the?Indian subcontinent,?southeast Asia,?islands?of the western?<a title=\"Pacific Ocean\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pacific_Ocean\">Pacific Ocean</a>, and eastern?Africa. <i>Casuarina</i>?is widely used as a?<a title=\"Bonsai\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bonsai\">bonsai</a>?subject, particularly in South-east Asia and parts of the?<a title=\"Caribbean\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caribbean\">Caribbean</a>. Indonesian specimens and those cultivated in?<a title=\"Taiwan\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taiwan\">Taiwan</a>?are regarded among the best in the bonsai world. The wood of this tree is used for shingles, fencing, and is said to make excellent hot-burning firewood.</span></span></span></span></div>\r\\n</div>\r\\n<div></div>\r\\n<div></div>\r\\n<div class=\"jzS ujU un8 TB_\">\r\\n<div class=\"Rnj hs0 un8 C9i\"><span class=\"tBJ dyH iFc sAJ O2T zDA IZT swG\"><span class=\"tBJ dyH iFc sAJ O2T zDA IZT swG\"><span class=\"richPinInformation\"><span class=\"tBJ dyH iFc j1A O2T zDA IZT swG\"> At Online Plants we have the largest retail range of this unusual native shrub. Excellent in well drained, sandy soils. They are unusual for their elongated thorn like foliage and also used as an ornamental purpose. <a href=\"https://www.pinterest.com.au/pin/490329478177175759/\">Casuarina </a></span></span></span></span><span class=\"tBJ dyH iFc sAJ O2T zDA IZT swG\"><span class=\"richPinInformation\"><span class=\"tBJ dyH iFc j1A O2T zDA IZT swG\">have the ability to grow and develop extensive root systems in very poor or sandy soils, and to completely cover the ground with its \"needles\", it is often used to stabilize soils in erosion prone areas or on sand dunes.</span></span></span></div>\r\\n</div>\r\\n<div></div>\r\\n<div></div>\r\\nCasuarinaceae, the beefwood family of dicotyledonous flowering plants, with two genera (Casuarina, 30 species; Gymnostoma, 20 species) of trees and shrubs, many of which have a distinctly pinelike aspect when seen from afar.\r\\n<h3><span class=\"_2PHJq public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\"><strong>How to grow:</strong></span></h3>\r\\n<p id=\"viewer-2pckm\" class=\"mm8Nw _1j-51 _1atvN _1FoOD _3M0Fe _2WrB- _1atvN public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr\"><span class=\"_2PHJq public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\"><strong>Lights</strong>: Casuarina plant loves to grow in bright light.</span></p>\r\\n<p id=\"viewer-9o6od\" class=\"mm8Nw _1j-51 _1atvN _1FoOD _3M0Fe _2WrB- _1atvN public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr\"><span class=\"_2PHJq public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\"><strong>Watering</strong>: Water every alternate day.</span></p>\r\\n<strong> Fertilizers:</strong> Use organic fertilizer, in every 3 months.', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '[]', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 0, '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '999', '1249', 'Agoho pine, Australian Pine, Casuarina Plant, Variegated Casuarina Plant', '', '', '', '', '', 'hanging-casuarina-plant', ''),
(933, 0, 'Chikoo / sapodilla (Variegated, Graft) Fruit Plant', 'simple', 'CK-3545-1', '<ul class=\"list-unstyled\">\r\\n  <li>?Live chiku plant along with the plastic pot.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?Plant height with pot is 18-24 inches and pot size is 6 inches.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?plant nature is outdoor, grows like tree, less watering.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?Grafted plant, starts fruiting in 2-3 years.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?Commonly known as sapodilla, sapota, chikoo, chiku.</li>\r\\n</ul>', '<h2 class=\"product_title entry-title wd-entities-title\">Chikoo / Sapodilla (Variegated, Graft) Fruit Plant</h2>\r\\nChiku is a tropical fruit. It has an uncanny resemblance to kiwifruit in color and skin texture, except the chiku is slightly larger and without the hairy feel, but rough. The rounder variety which I planted does not look like kiwifruit except for the color. Chiku is spelt differently in different countries, but retaining the same pronunciation. Other names for chiku are sawo (Indonesia), sapota (part of India), lamoot (Thailand, Laos and Cambodia), sapote, sapodilla, zapote, sapoti, nispero, dilly, naseberry, chico sapote, and many other names. In Malaysia, we called it chiku. Its scientific name is Manilkara zapota.\r\\n\r\\nThe Sapodilla (chiku) is native to Mexico, Central America and the Caribbean. It was first introduced to the Philippines by the Spaniards. Now the chiku is a common fruit in South East Asia, India and Pakistan.\r\\n<h3>Features of Plant</h3>\r\\nThe tree can grow to a height of 30 meters (100 feet) high. However, a grafted plant can be controlled to a low height. The tree is very hardy fruiting easily throughout the year, although the fruits take a long time to ripen. The flowers are minute and white in color.\r\\n\r\\n<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manilkara_zapota\">Sapodilla</a> , popularly known in India as Chiku. In India, it is cultivated for fruits that are liked all over the country. The fruit is a fleshy berry, variable in shape, size, and weight (75-150g). The skin is thin, rusty brown somewhat scurfy looking like Irish potato, and the pulp soft, melting, crumbling with a sandy or granular texture with 1-5 hard, black seeds.\r\\n\r\\nGet in touch with us for small quantities for your rear garden, kitchen garden, home garden or large quantities for farmland development, fruit orchards, fruit farms, real estate layouts or commercial cultivation.\r\\n<h3><strong>Health benefits of Chiku</strong></h3>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n  <li>As with most fruits, Chiku has lots of beneficial nutrients and minerals.</li>\r\\n  <li>Chiku has a special compound called tannin which has anti-bacterial, anti-parasitic, and anti-viral properties.</li>\r\\n  <li>It has large amounts of vitamin A, vitamin B, and vitamin C. Vitamin A is good for the eyes, strengthening eye vision. Vitamin B helps to overcome fatigue and stress. And everyone knows the benefits of vitamin C, chief of which is the strengthening of the immune system.</li>\r\\n  <li>Chiku contains lots of dietary fiber. Fiber helps to maintain HEALTHY WEIGHT, relieve constipation and lowering the risk of diabetes and heart disease.</li>\r\\n  <li>The main minerals found in chiku are copper, niacin, iron, calcium, and phosphorus. Iron, calcium, and phosphorus are bone-strengthening minerals.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>Care of Chikoo / Sapodilla Plant</h3>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n  <li><b>Soil: The pH of the soil should be around 6 to 8</b>. Shallow clay type of soil is not suitable for Sapodilla farming.</li>\r\\n  <li><strong>Humidity:</strong> Sapodilla is a tropical fruit and needs warm, humid climate for growth and development. The Sapodilla trees grow well up to an altitude of 1000 m.</li>\r\\n  <li><strong>Sunlight:</strong> the Sapodilla tree growth in direct proportion to the amount of light received.?<b>Sapodilla trees prefer bright light and direct sun</b></li>\r\\n  <li><b>Pot : </b>Sapota trees grow well in pot as long as you provide an adequate size pot for root development. Select a pot 18 to 24 plus inches in diameter and 20 plus inches in Sapota height, with adequate drain holes.</li>\r\\n  <li><strong>Water:</strong> Water alternately, Do not too moist the soil.</li>\r\\n</ul>', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '[]', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 0, '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '699', '999', 'chikoo, chiku, fruit, lamoot, Sapodilla, sapote, zapote', '', '', '', '', '', 'chikoo-sapodilla-variegated-graft-fruit-plant', '');
