(1010, 0, 'Pack of Terrarium Mini Plants', 'simple', 'Terra-Com-115', '<ul>\r\\n  <li><span data-sheets-value=\"{\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{\">Plant height 10-12 inches with 4\" inches pot.</span></li>\r\\n  <li>Best foliage plants & decorative plants.</li>\r\\n  <li>Low maintenance plant</li>\r\\n  <li>Beautiful color texture on leaves.</li>\r\\n  <li>Used for decorating corner, table top etc.</li>\r\\n</ul>', '<div>\r\\n<h2>Pack of Terrarium Mini Plants</h2>\r\\n<h3>What makes it special</h3>\r\\n<strong>A terrarium is a sealed ecosystem that acts as a <a href=\"https://nurserynisarga.in/?s=miniature&post_type=product&dgwt_wcas=1\">miniature</a> tropical climate</strong>.\r\\n\r\\nSo the best terrarium plants?are?tropical plants that are well adapted to that environment ? lovers of?humidity, moisture, warmth, and indirect sunlight\r\\n<ul data-slot-rendered-dynamic=\"true\">\r\\n  <li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrarium\">Terrariums?</a>can make indoor spaces more lively and inviting. They are also quite versatile in size?you can either go big or stay minimalistic with them.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h5>Care instructions</h5>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n  <li>First select a good spot for your <a href=\"https://nurserynisarga.in/?s=terrarium&post_type=product&dgwt_wcas=1\">terrarium</a>!</li>\r\\n  <li>Water lightly only after the soil gets dry every 1-2 Weeks, depending on conditions. Never overwater! The key is to watch your terrarium closely until you understand its drying pattern. Too much watering can be worse for the plants than too little.</li>\r\\n  <li>Place in a bright area indoors, some direct sunlight is fine.</li>\r\\n  <li>When the plants get as big as you want, pinch off the newest growth to encourage bushier growth.</li>\r\\n  <li>Water at the base of the plants and not the leaves because they can rot easily.</li>\r\\n  <li>Enjoy your terrarium.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h4 class=\"nl-h2\">What you get</h4>\r\\n</div>\r\\n<table class=\"nl-prod-desc-table\">\r\\n<tbody>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<th><span xss=removed>Name</span></th>\r\\n<th><span xss=removed>Quantity</span></th>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td>\r\\n<p class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://nurserynisarga.in/product/zebra-haworthia-plant/\">Zebra Haworthia, Haworthia Fasciata</a></p>\r\\n</td>\r\\n<td>1</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td>\r\\n<p class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://nurserynisarga.in/product/jade-bonsai-plant-with-colored-pot/\">Jade Plant- Miniature Crassula Ovata</a></p>\r\\n</td>\r\\n<td>1</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td><a href=\"https://nurserynisarga.in/product/aralia-plant-golden-aralia/\">Variegated Golden Aralia plant ? Miniature</a></td>\r\\n<td>1</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td><a href=\"https://nurserynisarga.in/product/mini-syngonium-mini-pixie/\">Mini Syngonium , ?Mini Pixie?</a></td>\r\\n<td>1</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td><a href=\"https://nurserynisarga.in/product/philodendron-atom-plant/\">Philodendron Atom Plant, Thaumatophyllum Bipinnatifidum</a></td>\r\\n<td>1</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td><a href=\"https://nurserynisarga.in/product/maidenhair-fern-plant/\">Rabbit foot Fern, Davallia fejeensis</a></td>\r\\n<td>1</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td><a href=\"https://nurserynisarga.in/product/miniature-bamboo-palm-chamaedorea-elegans/\">Parlour Palm | Bamboo palm | Chamaedorea Elegans ? Plant</a></td>\r\\n<td>1</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</table>\r\\n ', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '[]', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 0, '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1999', '2399', 'Terrarium, Terrarium mini plant', '', '', '', '', '', 'pack-of-terrarium-mini-plants', ''),
(1011, 0, 'Philodendron ?Red King? Plant', 'simple', 'PBRKING-1-1-5', 'Amazing leaves transformation from Red to Orange then Yellow to finally Green. A really showy plant with a lot to offer.\r\\n<ul>\r\\n  <li>Live plant along with a plastic pot.</li>\r\\n  <li>Plant height is 12-14 inches with 6 inches pot.</li>\r\\n  <li>Plants nature is indoor/semi shade, less watering.</li>\r\\n  <li>Best foliage plants, useful for tabletop and gift plants.</li>\r\\n</ul>', '<h2 class=\"product_title entry-title\">Philodendron ?Red King?</h2>\r\\n<h5><strong>Description</strong></h5>\r\\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Many of the traditional philodendron varieties are vines perfect for growing on a totem, up a trellis, or in a hanging basket and some offer pleasing variegated foliage. These are counted as some of the most easy to grow houseplants of all time. Most philodendrons vines grow in trees in their native tropical habitat, thus the common name, which translates as ?tree-lover.? Most form aerial roots, which in the wild help them climb trees.</span></p>\r\\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Philodendron is a classic, and practically no-fail houseplant because it?s so easy to grow. The philodendron family is a pretty big one, too ? so you can find a variety of plants that grow in a range of shapes, sizes, and colors.</span></p>\r\\nPhilodendron Red King is?<b>a rosette hybrid great for containers and as a indoor plant</b>. Philo Red King has a kaleidoscope of foliage colors. The new leaves come out a bright red color then fade to a more orange as some point they tend to be a bit yellow then finally turn more green. Red King is a philodendron hybrid that grows up to 3 feet tall. It is self-heading rather than vining, with the large leaves growing from a center base. A really showy plant with a lot to offer.\r\\n\r\\n \r\\n<h3 class=\"product_title entry-title\">Philodendron Usage</h3>\r\\nPhilodendron red king is a beautiful plant that can be <span class=\"s1\">grow well in most indoor light conditions at normal room temperature or slightly warmer. They </span>use to brighten up any room in your house. It grows quickly, making it a great choice for those who want a low-maintenance plant.\r\\n\r\\n<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philodendron\">Philodendron</a> \'Red King\'?<b>doesn\'t require additional humidity</b>. Plants absorb most water through their root system rather than their leaves, so the best way to provide humidity for your plants is through watering the soil. <span class=\"s1\">Allow the soil surface to dry to the touch between waterings. </span>Philodendron \'Red King\' does best in well-draining soil.\r\\n<h3><strong>Care and Maintenance</strong></h3>\r\\nBoth the <a href=\"https://nurserynisarga.in/?s=Philodendron&post_type=product&dgwt_wcas=1\">Philodendron</a> red king are easy to care for and require very little maintenance. These plants are fast-growing and can quickly become pot-bound, so be sure to repot them every year or two. It?s also a good idea to trim back any long, leggy stems to encourage new growth.\r\\n\r\\nThe Philodendron red king is a very easy plant to care for indoors. Here are a few tips to keep in mind:\r\\n<ol type=\"1\">\r\\n  <li>Water your plant regularly and never allow the soil to dry out completely.</li>\r\\n  <li>Fertilize your plant once or twice a year with a balanced, all-purpose fertilizer.</li>\r\\n  <li>Repot your plant every two or three years, using fresh, loose, airy soil that is rich in organic matter.</li>\r\\n  <li>Be sure to place your plant in a location that has indirect light. Avoid direct sunlight, as this can scorch the leaves.</li>\r\\n</ol>', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '[]', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 0, '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1050', '1300', 'Philodendron, Philodendron ?Red King?', '', '', '', '', '', 'philodendron-red-king-plant', ''),
(1012, 0, 'Conocarpus Lancifolius, Lanceleaf Buttonwood', 'simple', 'But-Lanci-254-01', 'The tree is used as an ornamental plant and in bonsai. Its flowers attract butterflies, bees, and other pollinators.\r\\n<ul class=\"list-unstyled\">\r\\n  <li>Live plant along with Plastic pot.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>The plants\' height with pot is 24-36 inches & pot size is 6 inches in diameter.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>The plants\' nature is Outdoor/semi-shade, with less watering.</li>\r\\n  <li>Mostly used as landscaping.</li>\r\\n  <li>Grows up to 20-40 feet and wide 6-12 meters.</li>\r\\n  <li>Propagate by seeds or cutting.</li>\r\\n  <li>Will tolerate shearing.</li>\r\\n</ul>', '<h2>Conocarpus Lancifolius, Lanceleaf Buttonwood</h2>\r\\n<i><b>Conocarpus lancifolius</b></i>, one of two species in the genus?<i>Conocarpus</i>, is a?tree?in the family?Combretaceae?native to coastal and riverine areas of?Somalia,?Djibouti, and?Yemen. It is found throughout the?Horn of Africa, the?Arabian peninsula, and?South Asia.\r\\n\r\\nThe tree has no common name in English. In?Somali, it is called?<i>qalab</i>\r\\n\r\\nThe tree\'s wood is dense and suitable for charcoal. Goats use the young trees and shoots as fodder, although the leaves contain tannin. Because of its high salt tolerance and relative drought tolerance, the tree is sometimes planted as a pioneer species in reforestation projects in its native habitat.\r\\n\r\\nThe tree has a symmetrical growth habit and can easily be shaped into a variety of different forms. It can be shaped into short and tall hedges and is effective for creating a visual or a noise barrier. With suitable plant spacing, it can also be grown as a hardy single-stemmed tree which is good for shade.\r\\n\r\\nThe tree has been extensively used in Karachi for landscaping along roads and by homeowners as a tall hedging tree for screening purposes. The tree thrives exceptionally well in the hot and dry climate of the city. The leaves of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conocarpus_lancifolius\">conocarpus lancifolius</a> have an anti-diabetic effect.\r\\n<h4>Conocarpus Lancifolius, plant & care</h4>\r\\nSunlight: Direct sunlight, Semi shade\r\\n\r\\nWatering: Water it morning, when the soil feels dry to the touch.\r\\n\r\\nSoil: Rich, well-drained soil.\r\\n\r\\nFertilizer: Spring season is good for fertilization, Use Organic fertilizer.', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '[]', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 0, '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '599', '999', 'conocarpus, Conocarpus Lancifolius, Lanceleaf Buttonwood', '', '', '', '', '', 'conocarpus-lancifolius-lanceleaf-buttonwood', ''),
