(1061, 0, 'Set of 5 Christmas Plant?', 'simple', 'GUAPACK-102-1-1', 'This pack contains Fruit Plant for Terrace/Open garden. Best plants for Planting fruit trees could prove to be the most fruitful effort in your <a href=\"https://parenting.firstcry.com/articles/magazine-10-surprising-benefits-of-gardening-growing-plants-is-beyond-just-a-good-hobby/?ref=interlink\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">gardening</a> endeavour. With their lush foliage, fragrant flowers, and nectar-like harvest, small fruit trees in your tiny garden could be the best investment for your home.\\n<ul>\\n  <li>Get organic food</li>\\n  <li>Easy to care for.</li>\\n</ul>', '<div>\\n<h2>Set of 5 Christmas Plant</h2>\\n<h3>What makes it special</h3>\\nAs the weather gets colder and the holidays draw near, many of us begin to transform our homes into festive, cheerful spaces.\\n\\nLike all house plants, these beautiful Christmas plants add an extra feeling of warmth and life in the home, something we can all appreciate when the nights are long and dark.\\n<p xss=removed><span xss=removed>Nursery Nisarga present combo pack of 5 lovely living decorations for yourselves, consider giving a plant as a Christmas gift.</span></p>\\n\\n<h4>Care instructions</h4>\\nThese plants are elementary to take care of, require very low maintenance.\\n\\nPlace the plant in Indoor or semi-shade area.\\nDo not overwater the plant, or water when the upper soil seems dry.\\nRemove dead, infected or damaged plant parts\\nFertilize your plant with organic fertilizer.\\n<h4 class=\"nl-h2\">What you get</h4>\\n</div>\\n<table class=\"nl-prod-desc-table\" xss=removed width=\"604\">\\n<tbody>\\n<tr>\\n<th><span xss=removed>Name</span></th>\\n<th><span xss=removed>Quantity</span></th>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>\\n<p class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://nurserynisarga.in/product/poinsettia-plant-christmas-flower/\">Poinsettia plant- Christmas flower</a></p>\\n</td>\\n<td><span xss=removed>1</span></td>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>\\n<p class=\"entry-title\"></p>\\n</td>\\n<td><span xss=removed>1</span></td>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>\\n<p class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://nurserynisarga.in/product/buy-christmas-tree-plant-online-nursery-nisarga/\">Christmas Tree Plant, Cook-pine</a></p>\\n</td>\\n<td><span xss=removed>1</span></td>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>\\n<p class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://nurserynisarga.in/product/christmas-cactus-schlumbergera-plant/\">Christmas Cactus, Thanksgiving Cactus ? Plant</a></p>\\n</td>\\n<td><span xss=removed>1</span></td>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>\\n<p class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://nurserynisarga.in/product/golden-cyprus/\">Golden Cyprus, Golden Cypress Plant</a></p>\\n</td>\\n<td><span xss=removed>1</span></td>\\n</tr>\\n</tbody>\\n</table>', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '[]', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 0, '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '2999', '3999', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'set-of-5-christmas-plant', ''),
(1062, 0, 'White Champa - Plumeria Alba (White)', 'simple', 'PLUWH-153-21', '<ul class=\"list-unstyled\">\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?Live plant along with Plastic pot</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?plants height with pot is 12-18 inches and pot size is 6 inches diameter.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?plants\' nature is outdoor, love full sun & less watering.</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?Aromatic plant, useful for shrubs, garden plants & gifts</li>\r\\n  <li><i class=\"fa fa-check-circle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>?Annual Flowering & hardy plant</li>\r\\n</ul>', '<div id=\"tab-description\" class=\"tab-pane tab-content active\">\r\\n<h3>White Champa - Plumeria Alba (White)</h3>\r\\nA plumeria is a fast-growing tropical tree that produces masses of fragrant blooms through out the year. A small tree, the plumeria reaches heights of about 30 feet at maturity. Also known as frangipani, a plumeria is a warm-climate plant hardy suitable to the Indian climate. Although the plant won\'t tolerate freezing winter climates, it can be planted in a container and brought indoors when the weather turns cold. Plumeria grow profusely in Hawaii, and is a popular flower choice for leis.\r\\n<h5><strong>Planting and Caring</strong></h5>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n  <li>Purchase a healthy plumeria tree at a Nursery Nisarga. Select a compact plumeria plant with an even, bright color and a sturdy, straight trunk. Look for evenly-spaced branches. Avoid plants with wilted leaves or poor color.</li>\r\\n  <li>Position the plumeria where the tree will be exposed to bright sunlight for at least 4 to 6 hours every day. Choose a planting location where the soil drains well and water doesn\'t puddle after rainfall. Avoid locations where the plumeria will be exposed to heat radiating off a brick or concrete wall.</li>\r\\n  <li>Plant a plumeria in a sturdy container filled almost to the top with a good quality commercial cactus mix or all-purpose potting mix. Use a container at least 6 to 10 inches (15 to 25 cm) in diameter. Be sure to use a container with a hole in the bottom to provide soil drainage, as a plumeria won\'t do well with wet feet.</li>\r\\n  <li>Water a plumeria deeply, then don\'t water it again until the soil is dry. Decrease watering when the weather cools in autumn and stop watering completely during the winter months. Resume normal watering when you can see new growth in spring.</li>\r\\n  <li>Feed a plumeria a high-nitrogen granular fertilizer with a ratio such as 32-6-2 every 2 to 3 weeks, beginning when new growth appears in spring. Change to a high phosphorus granular fertilizer with a ratio such as 10-50-10 in early May, and continue feeding the plant with the high phosphorus fertilizer every 2 to 3 weeks until August. Don\'t fertilize the plumeria after September 1.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>Short Description</h3>\r\\n<table class=\"agnis_table_01\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"5\">\r\\n<tbody>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<th>Plant Regional Name</th>\r\\n<td>White Plumeria Alba</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<th>Plant Common Name</th>\r\\n<td>White Plumeria, Champa White, Khairchapha</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<th>Category</th>\r\\n<td>Trees, Shrubs</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<th>Plant Sunlight Need</th>\r\\n<td>Sun Growing, Semi Shade</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<th>Plant Water Need</th>\r\\n<td>Normal, Can tolerate less, Can tolerate more</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<th>Plant Flowering Season</th>\r\\n<td>Year-around flowering, Flowers in flushes throughout the year</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</table>\r\\n</div>', '', '', 0, 0, '', '', '[]', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, 0, '0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '599', '649', 'Champa White, Khairchapha, white champa, White Plumeria, white plumeria alba', '', '', '', '', '', 'white-champa-plumeria-alba-white', '');
